All files compile OK. Here's a summary of the changes made to fix the AttributeError: 'CurrentUser' object has no attribute 'get' error:

Root cause: get_current_user was returning a CurrentUser Pydantic model, but all route handlers were using .get() dict-style access on it.

Fixes across 5 files:

app/models/dto_schemas.py — Added user_id: Optional[str] and collection_agents: Optional[Dict[str, List[str]]] fields to CurrentUser model.

app/core/dependencies.py — Changed return type to dict, calls user.model_dump() so all downstream code gets a plain dict with .get() access working.

app/controllers/auth_controller.py — Added derive_collection_agents() static method to extract the {"RMS": ["creator", ...], ...} map from the access_tree structure.

app/routes/auth_route.py — Added collection_agents to the JWT payload during login (derived from access_tree). Removed unused CurrentUser import.

app/routes/agent_route.py — Rebuilt the endpoints to build collections from the access_tree via AuthController.derive_collection_agents() instead of expecting collection_agents in the old JWT payload.

app/routes/chat_route.py — Changed current_user.collection_agents to current_user.get("collection_agents") (dict-style access).

app/controllers/chat_controller.py — No changes needed; already uses .get() dict access.
